    "Conditional probability tells us, for example, the probability that the person will have a cloudy",
    "1 3 X-ray given that we know they have Cancer, written as P(XRay|Cancer) foot_0 where \"|\" means \"given\".",
    "Conditional independence tells us which variables are irrelevant to that probability.",
